Today was all about getting hands-on with Linux and learning essential Command Line Interface (CLI) commands. Working in the terminal gave me a deeper understanding of how Linux operates beyond the GUI, and I can already see how powerful and efficient the CLI can be.

Key Takeaways:
- Practiced basic Linux commands for navigation, file management, and system operations.
- Learned how to use the CLI to interact with the system efficiently.
- Gained confidence in working without a graphical interface, reinforcing the importance of CLI skills in cybersecurity and system administration.

Final Thoughts:
Working in Linux and using CLI commands felt like unlocking a new level of control over the system. Mastering these skills will be crucial as I continue my journey in cybersecurity and IT. Looking forward to learning more advanced commands and scripting.
